%S A326730 0,1,3,2,5,4,6,3,7,6,8,5,10,7,9,4,9,8,10,7,12,9,11,6,14,11,13,8,15,10,
%T A326730 12,5,11,10,12,9,14,11,13,8,16,13,15,10,17,12,14,7,18,15,17,12,19,14,
%U A326730 16,9,21,16,18,11,20,13,15,6,13,12,14,11,16,13,15,10,18,15,17,12,19,14,16,9,20,17,19,14,21,16,18,11,23,18,20,13,22,15,17,8,22,19,21,16,23
%N A326730 Number of iterations of A326729(x) starting at x = n to reach 0.
%C A326730 The sequence is well-defined, see Problem 5 of IMO 2019.
%C A326730 From _Natalia L. Skirrow_, May 24 2026: (Start)
%C A326730 The maximum a(n) for n in the range [0..2^l) is binomial(l+1,2), achieved by n = 2^l-2^floor(l/2) = A122746(l-1).
%C A326730 Sum_{n=0..2^l-1} a(n)   = 2^(l-2)*l*(l+1) = A001788(l).
%C A326730 Sum_{n=0..2^l-1} a(n)^2 = 2^(l-4)*l*(l+1)*(l+2)*(l+1/3).
%C A326730 Thus, the waiting time for an n uniformly sampled in [0..2^l) has expectation l*(l+1)/4 and variance l*(l+1)*(l+1/2)/12.
%C A326730 If n is written as the binary word 1^(o_0) 0^(z_0) 1^(o_1) ..., then (with O_i = Sum_{j=0..i} o_j), a(n) = Sum_i 2*O_i*z_i + o_i. (End)
%H A326730 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A326730/b326730.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8192</a>
%H A326730 International Mathematical Olympiad, <a href="https://www.imo-official.org/problems.aspx">Problem 5 of IMO 2019</a>.
%H A326730 Rémy Sigrist, <a href="/A326730/a326730.png">Scatterplot of the ordinal transform of the first 2^16 terms</a>
%F A326730 a(n) = 2*A029931(n) - A000120(n)^2.
%F A326730 a(2*n) = a(n) + 2*A000120(n), a(2*n+1) = a(n)+1. - _Natalia L. Skirrow_, May 24 2026
%e A326730 326730_10 = 1001111110001001010_2, whose run-length sequences are o = 1,6,1,1,1 and z = 2,3,2,1,1 with O = 1,7,8,9,10, so a(326730) = Sum_i 2*O_i*z_i+o_i = 2*1*2+1 + 2*7*3+6 + 2*8*2+1 + 2*9*1+1 + 2*10*1+1 = 126. - _Natalia L. Skirrow_, May 24 2026
%o A326730 (PARI) A326730(n) = my(b=Vecrev(binary(n)), m=vecsum(b)); 2*sum(i=1,#b,i*b[i]) - m^2;
%o A326730 (Python)
%o A326730 A326730=lambda n: n and A326730(n>>1)+(2*n.bit_count())**(~n&1) # _Natalia L. Skirrow_, May 24 2026
%o A326730 (Python)
%o A326730 def a(n): return 2*sum(i for i, bi in enumerate(bin(n)[2:][::-1], 1) if bi == "1") - n.bit_count()**2 # _Michael S. Branicky_, May 24 2026
%Y A326730 Cf. A000120, A029931, A326729, A326731, A326732.
%K A326730 base,nonn,changed
%O A326730 0,3
%A A326730 _Max Alekseyev_, Jul 22 2019
